  <text>
    <body>
      <ab type="lido:objectWorkType">Poster</ab>
      <ab subtype="creation" type="lido:event">
        <date>1979</date>
      </ab>
      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">The upper section of the red-framed poster displays the Albanian film title in colourful letters on a white background and its Serbo-Croatian equivalent ‘Kad proleće kasni’ (When spring comes late). The name of the Pristina-based production company ‘Kosovafilmi’ appears centre left. The middle column features the name of Kosovo-Albanian director Ekrem Kryeziu. The column to the right displays the names of the screenwriters, main actors, theme music composer and cameraman.</ab>
      <ab subtype="comment" type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">The feature was released in 1979 and was the first Albanian-language film produced in socialist Yugoslavia.</ab>
